<h2>Make your creative briefs count</h2>
<p>This might seem like a lot of information, but remember that each of these steps shouldnâ€™t take more than a paragraph. Your creative briefs should be compactâ€”short and sweet documents that contain everything you need to know about a marketing project in process in just a few pages.</p>
<p>Hereâ€™s how to write a creative brief in 9 simple steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Write a project overview</li>
<li>Define the project objectives</li>
<li>Share your brandâ€™s key message and facts</li>
<li>Describe your target market</li>
<li>Summarize your brand guidelines</li>
<li>Point out your competitors</li>
<li>Include any references for inspiration</li>
<li>Spell out the timeline and deliverables</li>
<li>State your distribution plan</li>
</ol>
<p>Follow these steps for less back-and-forth with your team and fewer creative revisionsâ€”and more time to focus on how to put your amazing creative to use.</p>
