<div id="keyword"></div>
<h3>3. Keyword competitive analysis</h3>
<p>A keyword competitive analysis will take your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/keyword-research-for-ppc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">keyword research</a> to the next level. With it, you look at your organic and/or paid keywords in comparison to those of your competitors.</p>
<p>The idea is to find out <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2012/11/14/how-to-rank-for-a-keyword">what keywords are realistic to target</a> to outrank your competitors and which ones are not. Because targeting keywords youâ€™re not going to rank forâ€”whether for SEO or PPC, is a waste of time and budget.</p>
<h4>Keyword competitive analysis example</h4>
<p>Letâ€™s say you are a communication platform that streamlines email, text, and phone communication for home improvement businesses. Your bread and butter (your S in SWOT, if you will) is text automation, and you want to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/21/how-to-run-google-ads">start running PPC ads </a>for it. Perfect opportunity to do a paid keyword competitive analysis.</p>
<p>There are plenty of<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/11/09/competitor-keywords"> tools to help you find competitor keywords</a>.</p>
<p>For this example, I put Podiumâ€™s domain into Semrush, filtered for keywords NOT containing â€œpodium,â€ and that have an average position of one, then sorted by traffic to the corresponding landing page.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/competitive-analysis-keyword-analysis.webp" alt="keyword competitive analysis in ahrefs" width="922" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76077" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/competitive-analysis-keyword-analysis.webp 922w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/competitive-analysis-keyword-analysis-480x311.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 922px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>As you can see, the top keywords include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reviews for google (310 visits a month)</li>
<li>Converge pay (310)</li>
<li>Online reputation management (310)</li>
<li>Hvac marketing (169)</li>
</ul>
<p>â€œSms marketingâ€ is further down the list at 70 visits per month.</p>
<p>It appears as though Podium is more interested in <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/what-is-reputation-management/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">online reputation management </a>and payment processing, so this could be an opportunity for me. Also, withâ€ HVAC marketingâ€ getting comparable traffic, I might want to look further and see if this is a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/niche-markets/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">niche</a> Podium specializes in or if this is a particularly fruitful market.</p>
